{{Expand German|Bernard Crespi|date=January 2016|topic=bio}}
'''Bernard J. Crespi''' {{post-nominals|country=CAN|FRSC}} is a professor of [[evolutionary biology]] at [[Simon Fraser University]]. His research focuses on [[social evolution]] across multiple scales, using genetic and ecological approaches.<ref>[https://www.sfu.ca/biology/faculty/crespi/index.html Dr. Bernard J. Crespi, Professor]</ref> He is one of the initiators of the [[imprinted brain theory]].

In 2010, he was elected as a fellow of the [[Royal Society of Canada]].<ref>[https://www.sfu.ca/archive-university-communications/media_releases/media_releases_archives/royal-society-of-canada-recognizes-sfu-biologist.html Royal Society of Canada recognizes SFU biologist]</ref>

